A teenager had to be freed by firefighters using a crowbar after she got her arm stuck in a letterbox when she tried to let herself in after a night out. 

Jordan Armstrong, 18, thought she would be able to open her sister's front door in Colchester, Essex, after she arrived in the early hours of the morning to find the door was locked.

The former Colchester Institute student had been to a party near to her sister Anja-Marie's home and needed somewhere to spend the night after she felt it would take her too long to walk home.  

