But she soon found she was unable to open the door and her friends called firefighters at 2.30am on Saturday to free her.

'I had a bit too much to drink and I couldn't walk all the way to my house so I thought I'd go and stay at my sister's but she wasn't home,' said Miss Armstrong. 

'As I was drunk, I thought my arm was bendy enough to open the door.

'The fire brigade and ambulance crew were absolutely amazing and even they had a laugh at my stupidity.

