'Thankfully I woke up in the morning and I was fine.'

Paramedics were also called to the scene and Miss Armstrong's friends took pictures of the teenager's predicament on smartphones before posting them online through instant messaging app Snapchat.

Her sister only discovered what had happened when she read about the story on the internet on Saturday morning.

A spokesman for the East of England Ambulance Service said: 'Medics remained at the scene but the patient was not taken to hospital.' 

 

 

 

